So one really important concept was the concept of a set.

00:08:31.300 --> 00:08:37.080
This is an idea that came from Cantor, and Cantor thought, well, a set is defined by a predicate,

00:08:37.320 --> 00:08:42.560
like, "is tall". "Is tall" defines the set of tall people.

00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:46.100
And the idea was, you give me a predicate, I'll give you a set.

00:08:46.480 --> 00:08:50.920
But Bertrand Russell, in his famous paradox, showed why that's not gonna work.

00:08:50.980 --> 00:08:55.180
He said, take the set of all things that aren't members of themselves.

00:08:55.460 --> 00:08:56.860
That's a predicate.

00:08:57.220 --> 00:09:00.620
